ut - we didn't have very many many presents, no. No. The one cousin I did have and that was from aunt - gave it to me, for me birthday, and it was a wax doll, that was a lovely doll, it was about - like that. And of course that couldn't sit near the fire 
w
ith it because it was wax. And so - but it was dressed beautiful with a frock and a sash, we used to - you know, one of these sashes we used to have round us and - of course I couldn't sit near the fire and then - then - I had a cradle given me, a - a sor
t
 of cradle - length - so that the doll'd go in, well instead of the wheels being like they are now they was just one block of wood with a hole in, with a nail through it. But they used to go round, they used to be shoved and go round and we used to think 
