Yes. All of them did, yes, all of it, yes. Used to be - up the Manor used to be two gardeners up there. Yes. Used to be nine of us in the house. Alone. Well you look at the vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 What about livestock, they didn't keep hens at the manor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 No, we kept pigs there. Pigs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 What about the other places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Oh - at - Port - Black Notley they used to keep their own hens. But at Porters Hall - ducks, because they had the moat, round the house. Yes
. But at the Manor that was the time when the pigs was at - on the go the cook used to have to salt them when they was - all hams you see or used to have to be dried. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 At Porters Hall did you have the same food or different food from the family?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Just the same as they had, just the same, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Was it the same or different at the Manor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
No, we used to - we had the same food as they did, the joint used to come off their table onto the servants hall. Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 At Porters Hall you ate in the servants hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Servants hall. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 While you were there can you remember any sort of musical evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
No, well we used to have - no - we - they used to have - 'cos they had the daughters - at home, and they used to
 have a dance sometimes, a dance. Used to take - it was a big - oh ever such a big room the dining room 'cos they got twenty-two chairs in it, and they was all very old - and it was all polished floor but when - it - they used to take the carpet up - butl
er and footman used to roll all this carpet up, and shut the table up and they used to dance in there. But that's the - family. When they asked friends.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Was this at the Manor?
