\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 At the Manor I was there -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 I mean at Porters Hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
No, I don't remember 'em playing games. Only tennis. Tennis used to play and - hockey, they used to have - at the Manor they used to have hockey afternoons, at the Manor, hockey, yes. You could see 'em playing. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 But not at Porters Hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
No, they didn't have much - she used to go out - I believe she used to go out to tennis, that's about all. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did they have a library there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Were they not very interested in reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 They had newspapers I expect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Used to read newspapers, yes, that's right, and they used to have books to - you know, one or two books to read but nothing - like other place.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 You never went away for a holiday with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did they go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
At the Manor? At Porters Hall? Not very often they'd go, they used to go occasionally but not very - I was the one that used to go to - Stebbing church. Yes. Even the cook didn't go, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did they say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 No. Nothing there at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 No family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
No, nothing of that, that was - nothing there, neither at the Manor - either. There was no family prayers there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 At Porters Hall were they interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Well - I really - I wasn't there very long you see, no. I don't remember that there, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 What about playing cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 No. No. No, they didn't used to, us girls used to - but - not they, no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did he go out hunting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
No, he used to - there used to be a farm you see, but I don't - he didn't have a horse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 He ran the farm did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
He ran the farm. Yes, he ran the farm. He used to have the - farm hands you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Would you call him a gentleman farmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Yes, a gentleman farmer, yes, they come there you see, he was in the - Yeomanry, and he came there and had this farm you see well then of course the war broke out and he had to go again you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did he have a kind of farm bailiff there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Yes. Yes. A foreman they used to call him, yes. Mm. Well then they sold up during the war, he got killed I think, he got killed in the end, 'cos I had to leave then, she was going to shut the house up you see, and so I left. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did his wife go out visiting by herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
No. No. She didn't go visiting, it was a lonely place really, Porters Hall, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did they not have people to come and visit them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 No, not much, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Very little entertaining there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 No, they didn't have much entertaining there at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Not even other officers or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 No, I don't remember other officer coming, no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did he belong to a club do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 No, I don't think they - Really better than I ca
n remember of today, you know what I mean. Can always remember years ago -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Can we go on to the Manor now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Yes, I'll go on to the Manor now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 At that stage I suppose you weren't wishing you were living at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 No, no, I was happy at th
e Manor. I was happy at the Manor, we made our own fun and that there, all of us there together, we made a - worked hard but we made our own fun together you know. Yes. It was very -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Do you think it was better because there were more of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Yes
, there was, yes, yes. Yes. Yes, there was a lot more of us, we used to sit up half the night us girls, with - with the butler and footman and that and - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14953070\charrsid14840390 
groom}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390  and gardener used to come in and play cards, and one thing an another. We used to - we used 
to play these cards and of course - the man that used to look after the gas used to create next morning so we - we got - so we used to buy our own candles. Because he was only allowed a certain amount of gas you see and if we kept that on too long well th
at was - they'd had it. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 You were telling me about the dances and so on there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did you say there was tennis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Nine. Nine of us in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 They played tennis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Oh tennis, yes. Yes. Yes, they played tennis - and cro
quet and - she used to go out hunting. They used to keep horses, oh yes. Not - Lady Flannery but the daughters used to go out hunting, yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did he not go hunting himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 No, he was up {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}
 every day, up to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} every day, he was MP yo
u see. He was MP, yes. But the - their daughters, one of - married a very rich man, he - she did, her names was - oh dear, whatever was it - hm - and the youngest one any rate, Eve her name was, she - was - married a poorer - a lef - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14953070\charrsid14840390 lieutenant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390  and they 
thought that was very poor. But any rate she was more happy than the other one, and - she used to got up there and us girls - not to say anything but she used to have this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14953070\charrsid14840390 lieutenant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390  come and visit her, and she used - she didn't used to want to go up to Lo
ndon with them when they went up during the week 'cos she'd got some excuse, she wanted to go hunting, 'cos she used to - didn't want to go hunting at all, she wanted to meet the young man. She was ever so good with us girls. Mm. She was really. She did m
a
rry him in the end but he got killed. Mm. But - she was very happy with him, she said, it doesn't matter, she said, about money as long as your happy, she used to say to us girls. Mm. But she had three - she had three children, she had three children, Dav
i
d - David and - oh I forget the other one's name now, but - I know I had to have my bicycle ready in the servants hall for when her boy came - came and to go running up to the doctor's to get him quick - 'cos they hadn't - he wouldn't have no phone on, no
t Sir Fortescue wouldn't there. He'd have it on at the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 house but he wouldn't have it on here, he said he'd be away from the phone. Yes. Yes. Funny he wouldn't have it on, but - so we had to - run off - I - had my bicycle there ready when the child wa
s born and - and they - used to - I had to go for the doctor, yes, I remember that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did they used the phone a lot in the house in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Yes. Yes they used to use the phone a lot, yes. You see, he was MP and his - he used to go up Mon
day mornings and come back Friday - Friday nights you see, well then - gradually all the staff had to keep going to the war you see and was left so that she had to manage herself up in London and I was left down here to cook. Sometimes I'd go up with her 
- and - if the - there's only one at the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 house and - I used to have to go up and do a bit of cooking up there you see. Yes. Used to be interesting work though. They used to be glad to get out of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. Oh dear, it's when the motor car started first you seem 'cos the driver - and what with these cars and the trams you know, oh the busy streets. I used to clutch the side there and - oh I wasn't I glad when I got to - 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Brentwood{\*\xmlclose}. Yes. Mm hm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did they play cards at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 No. No, they didn't pla
y cards, no, only us girls in the kitchen used to do that. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did you ever go away with them for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
No. No, I never went away with them, no. No. No. No. They very rare went away for a holiday. No, very rare, I - I never known 'em much to go away. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did they go out together when he was done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Oh when they was down here, yes, they used to go out together, and she used - he used to go round the farms you see as well 'cos all this \{BLANK\} nearly belonged to him. All the farms you
 see, the - there was - Russells farm, Brook Farm, Parsnips Farm, Priory Farm - Bibles Farm - Sandhills - there there's another one somewhere. Hacksall, all belonged to him you see, and so he used to go all round to the farmers, you see, make a call on th
e
m - and that, and he used to charge very little rent for them. Yes. And then she'd go round all for the poor, she; was very good to the poor in the village she was. She'd go round - round the alms houses, I believe she used to give a half a pint of milk e
v
ery day to the - there was four alms houses, they were supplied with their milk everyday from the Brook Farm. She used to pay for it. And she'd go round to see if anybody was - sick you see and she'd send 'em soup, the cook used to have to do all soup and
 
sorts of things and get the - the gardener to take it to them you see. Yes. Sometimes she'd them a rabbit or whatever she could - fruit out the garden, you see. Yes. She was very good in that way. Yes, she was, very good to the people. They missed her ver
y
 much. Yes. And when the boys went to the war - when the boys went to the war - Sir Fortescue made all their wages up to them. 'Cos they didn't get so much in the army as what they was earning, so he made all their wages up to them while they was away - w
h
ile they was at war. Yes. Yes. He did. He belonged to the Cables, there was a big cable man. Yes. Besides being an MP and that, yes. Do you remember hearing about the Titanic? That was - one his does what he'd done. Yes. Yes. He - no, it went down in the 
e
nd, but it was - oh he was upset about that because he done the - mm - all the cables and one thing and another. But it got hit by bomb didn't it. Oh that - that's right, iceberg, that's right, yes. Yes, it did, yes, I remember that, oh he was upset about
 
that, yes. Yes, very upset. Mm. But - you know it - they was very good to us up there. 'Course we had be in a certain - ten o'clock there every night, ten o'clock yes. Yes. If - if us girls went to a party or anything - we used to say to the other one, le
ave the door unlocked, put all the lights out, leave the door unlocked at the back door and in we'd creep upstairs. Used to lock the door behind us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Was this in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Down here, down here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Where would you be going to a party then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Well at Christmas time you see people used to ask you out to parties, well it'd be eleven o'clock sometimes before you could leave you see, and that's when we - we used to do it, yes. She never did find - find out about it, no, 'cos we was alway
s cute about that. Yes. See their department was quite a way from us but sometimes she'd ring the bell you see, and be a whole row of bells, oh longer than this room, in - in the hall. Every room you see. 'Course if you wasn't there, well there you are. T
he one who had to answer it. But - we mostly was there, she - she was very good, she wouldn't ring after a certain time if she could help it. No. She didn't, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did she have much social life on her own in the week when he wasn't there?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Well 
she used to have people to tea and that you see, yes. She used to ask - people to tea, and then they was there - there's always a flag put up, but when they was away the flag was took down - so people'd know if they was there you see. If they had callers 
and - never know that they were coming you see, but - that's how they used to - people used to know when they was at home. The flag used to be up but when they was away the flag used to be down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 She went out calling herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Yes. Yes, she would, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Would she ever go out in the evenings by herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Beg pardon? No, no, no, she wouldn't go out in the evening, no, she wouldn't, no. No. No, she was - you know, there was people to dinner and that in the evenings, yes. Yes. Yes, they we
re very - you know, very nice really, yes. Can't grumble at that place - I can't grumble at the places I went to at all, only at that one at - Notley. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Where did you seep in all these places, was it always up in a sort of attic?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 No. Only
 at the - the London house, and that was right up tip top at the London house, Summers Place, but the other places we had all our own departments - we - three in one bedroom - used - at the Manor. One bedroom, and the - that was the cook, kitchen maid and
 
myself, we had - 'cos there was no more spare but the - then the butler by himself, the footman by himself - and - another - another two I think had to sleep together. See, 'cos I mean there was a lot to sleep wasn't there, yes. But we all each had our li
ttle bits in the room. See what I mean, we had our bed, it was all sort of divided - so you couldn't interfere with each others things. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 You had a sort of cupboard for your things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Yes. Yes, we all each had a cupboard. Yes, we did, we all eac
h had a cupboard. And we - each was stand you see. Yes. We had a bathroom but - we - have a bath only once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 You were allowed to only once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Yes, had a bath once a week, and we had to take it in turns you see 'cos of the hot water. Yes. But we used to have the wash stand in the room, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Could you put up photographs and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Oh yes, you could have - put up what you like in the room, yes. Have all your own little trinkets you know, what you wanted, yes. I used 
to - generally have a pot - fern or something on my table, I used to love flowers, anything, yes. And photographs, you could have your mother and father, who you liked, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 In the other places you had your own room without having to share did you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Yes. Yes, yes, I had me own room, yes, we did, yes. Cook had her -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 At Porters Hall and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Yes, we had our own room there, yes, we did, yes, and at - at Wickham Bishops too, yes. But - but it was the Manor, because of course there was a lot of us there you see that - yes. But when I was up {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London
{\*\xmlclose} you see - at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 house I had me own room there, up there. And the housekeeper, she used to have downstairs, she liked to be downstairs best, she had - sort of in the sitting room downstairs
 she had her bed, but she could have her belongings wherever she wanted 'em. She liked sleeping downstairs best. I don't know for why she did but she did. Mm. Yes. All in that time. I said I have mother. So she said, well it takes me so long, why have - w
h
y have you done it so quick? I said, well I don't know, I've done it, and - I said, but I have to dust twenty-two chairs, I said, even before you're up in the morning. And - I took her up the Manor one day and she was so thrilled to see all the - up the M
anor and what I had to do, I said, I do that before you're up in the morning. I don't \{ILLEGIBLE\} you, I generally have me cup of tea in bed now. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14953070\charrsid14840390 
And there she would be giving it this food - off of her plate and that, and her son had come home, Harold came,
 he used to grumble at her and say, having that cat on the - cat on the table, it's not right, he said, and she - that cat'd sit there and there that would sit there and she used to be feeding it, she'd keep giving it - take that, take that, and she'd ask
 - Sir - Sir Fortescue for more, or the butler rather - for more and it - he used to grumble at her. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
But the old cat knew, of course she didn't have to have it on when they had company I mean - in the - at the dining table, but that knew when that was compa
ny and that wasn't, that cat sat there still as a mouse. Oh dear. That cat. That's put me through at times - at night. Sometimes we'd let it out at night you see and used to - I used to have to get it in at night. Well - I thought, yes, I'm not going to b
e
 up 'til twelve o'clock trying to find that cat all round the - house in the - fir trees and that. So I used to - bring it into the butler's - pantry, used to push it in the drawer - and - let it go there, then I used to walk round the house with the - ca
t
 in me arms, puss, puss, puss I used to call out, and - all the time it hadn't been out, I used to make it do what it wanted to do in a box in the kit - in the pantry. We used to be artful years ago as well as they are now. She'd say, oh Bish you darling,
 you've come in - and had only been round in my arms. 'Cos she used to have such a lot of scent on her; see, and - if the cat hadn't been outside that sent still was on the cat. Dar oh dear. Used to have our games. Up at the Manor.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 There were keepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Oh yes, kept - gamekeeper, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 That would be in a separate cottage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Yes. Up at - what we used to call a Pest House. Yes. Yes. Oh they used to have great big parties when there used to be the pheasant shooting you see and partridge s
hooting. They used to have their lunch then up at the Dog. Cook used to have to make huge - meat puddings, used to be taken up at the Dog, all ready for all these - shooters to eat up there. Oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 What did they do with what they shot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Oh they
 used to go home in barrow loads. Then the shooters used to have what they want, and they used to be sent all off to friends - next day all labels used to be - have to be wrote out to the addresses they sent to, used to send them by - through post just as
 
they was with the labels round their neck. Yes. Often - oh dear, see the - there used to be the game larder you see and used to be all these hung up, rabbits and hares and pigeons and all sorts of things. Dear oh dear, yes. Oh whatever would they think of
 today, I mean - such places as that, then the Lady Flannery - she found a pearl in one of her oysters. And - Sir }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14953070\charrsid14840390 Fortescue}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390  had it done for her. Yes. Yes. But there was - I forget where the ice come from, it came in a sack. I don't know where it come from t
here must have been - don't know at all, but - the only time was summertime you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 You mean they'd keep the oysters fresh like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Yes, yes. Yes. Used to keep 'em fresh like that. They used to have a - they mustn't be kept after they're out of water much must they I don't think, no, you have to eat them straight away. Used to have these oysters when - friends come you see. 1 yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 They wouldn't put white wine on the ice then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 I forget about that. Mm. Forget about that, but any rate
 they - they used to - oh those oysters, I couldn't bear to see them eating 'em. Couldn't bear 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 Did they have a sort of cellar to keep things really cold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Yes. Yes. They had a cellar and all for the wines and that you see, yes. Sir Fortescue always used to keep the keys of the cellar. Always. They was not allowed out of his sight. But when he wanted a bottle of wine }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14953070\charrsid14840390 minded}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
 you he give 'em to the butler and the butler had to go down and get it. And bring the keys back to him straight away. Yes
. So - he knew exactly where it all was and he'd tell the butler where - exactly which place to get it from and everything, he used to check up all on the wine place - cellars, yes, how old, what year you see, yes. It had all got the dates on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 I suppo
se it would be quite easy to do a bit of a fiddle of that kind wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Yes. You couldn't fiddle him out of anything. No, he - you couldn't fiddle him about the wine bottles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2896308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 But there was quite a lot of that with milk and so on wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8743498 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3175380\charrsid14840390 
Oh yes, they used to fiddle 'em sometimes. Sometimes the butler'd come out, we've had a drink tonight, Sir Fortescue has given us a drink. It's what was left over it had to be drank up you see. Oh dear. That's how we used to have our - fun you see 
years ago used to have to make it. Mm. Dear oh dear. Mm.
\par }}